                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>
                        <p>There are many diagrams throughout the manuscript and the majority of the textblock is given over to tables.</p>
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>Extensive annotations throughout the entire textblock in a range of different hands all in Persian. </p>
                     <p>Before the text begins, there are also many comments, including a page in devanagari script under the Persian title "names of Hindavi letters" on f.ix. </p>
                  </additions>
